<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-18T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-18T18:00:00-05:00" n="543" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d543">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.515/60: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-18T19:00:00-04:00">March 18,
                                    1942—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>57. Your 62, March 8, 10 a.m. For McBride. The Treasury and War
                            Departments are in consultation regarding the currency problem and
                            expect to furnish us with a definite reply to your recommendation in the
                            near future. It is probable that your suggestions will in large measure
                            be adopted.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>